==English==
<!--===Pronunciation===-->
===Etymology===
Refers to the Greek myth of Eris and the [[golden apple]], which attracted the [[desire]]s of [[Hera]], [[Athena]], and [[Aphrodite]].

===Noun phrase===
'''[[apple]] of somebody’s [[eye]]''' (''Plural:'' '''apples of somebody’s eye''')

# {{idiom}} A favourite, a particular preference, or a loved one.
#: ''Sara was never the same after losing her daughter, the '''apple of Sara’s eyes'''.''

